: 264, \"to\": 308}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The cyclists had departed their plane and then strolled into the Beijing airport whilewearing the same cloth face masksthat became ubiquitous during the Covid-19 pandemic.\", \"from\": 314, \"to\": 485, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 379, \"end\": 386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999758730264365, \"rank\": 2.412755599574732e-05, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The cyclists\", \"from\": 314, \"to\": 326}, {\"ngram\": \"their plane\", \"from\": 340, \"to\": 351}, {\"ngram\": \"the same cloth face\", \"from\": 408, \"to\": 427}, {\"ngram\": \"masksthat\", \"from\": 428, \"to\": 437}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I understood why.\", \"from\": 486, \"to\": 503, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The smog in Beijing on the eve of the Games was godawful, and wearing a thin piece of cloth-or maybe a gas mask-seemed like a smart idea.\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 516, \"end\": 523, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999758730264365, \"rank\": 2.412755599574732e-05, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The smog\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 512}, {\"ngram\": \"the eve\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 534}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 547}, {\"ngram\": \"a thin piece\", \"from\": 574, \"to\": 586}, {\"ngram\": \"cloth\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 595}, {\"ngram\": \"maybe a gas mask\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 615}, {\"ngram\": \"a smart idea\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 640}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the action upset Chinese Olympics officials, who had promised to the world that the city's air would be scrubbed of pollution for the Games.\", \"from\": 642, \"to\": 786, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 663, \"end\": 670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.8436489098871665, \"rank\": 0.18532715439474962, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the action\", \"from\": 646, \"to\": 656}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 720}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's air\", \"from\": 726, \"to\": 740}, {\"ngram\": \"pollution\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 771}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 776, \"to\": 785}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They chided American officials, who scolded the cyclists, whoeventually apologized to the host nation.\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 799, \"end\": 807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4070824545063877e-17, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the cyclists\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 843}, {\"ngram\": \"the host nation\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Media seized on the kerfuffle, and before long,news storiesberthed backlash, thenbacklash to the backlash.\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 996, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Media\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 895}, {\"ngram\": \"the kerfuffle\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 919}, {\"ngram\": \"news\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 941}, {\"ngram\": \"backlash\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 965}, {\"ngram\": \"thenbacklash\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 979}, {\"ngram\": \"the backlash\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 995}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eventually, the imbroglio faded from memory after the competitions kicked off, and the whole ordeal became part of the long history of wacky Olympics drama.\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1153, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the imbroglio\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1022}, {\"ngram\": \"memory\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1040}, {\"ngram\": \"the competitions\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1063}, {\"ngram\": \"the whole ordeal\", \"from\": 1080, \"to\": 1096}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1108}, {\"ngram\": \"the long history\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1128}, {\"ngram\": \"wacky Olympics drama\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1152}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Olympics, you mix thousands of athletes with tens of thousands of journalists, sprinkle in global politics, add the pressure to perform and a few cross-culture barriers, and you end up with the perfect recipe for head-scratching controversies.\", \"from\": 1155, \"to\": 1405, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1170}, {\"ngram\": \"thousands\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1189}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1201}, {\"ngram\": \"tens of thousands\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1224}, {\"ngram\": \"journalists\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1239}, {\"ngram\": \"global politics\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1268}, {\"ngram\": \"the pressure\", \"from\": 1274, \"to\": 1286}, {\"ngram\": \"a few cross-culture barriers\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1330}, {\"ngram\": \"the perfect recipe\", \"from\": 1352, \"to\": 1370}, {\"ngram\": \"head-scratching controversies\", \"from\": 1375, \"to\": 1404}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of them even snowball into global media firestorms.\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1462, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"global media firestorms\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1461}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Who remembers swimmer Ryan Lochte and hisfabricated storyof being mugged at the 2016 Games in Brazil?\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1485, \"end\": 1496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Lochte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ryan Lochte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Lochte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Lochte\"}, {\"begin\": 1557, \"end\": 1563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"score\": 0.999132035231388, \"rank\": 0.0008687187632209423, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"hisfabricated storyof\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1522}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2016 Games\", \"from\": 1539, \"to\": 1553}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I bring this up because the 2024 Paris Games have just kicked off, and there is already plenty of bizarre drama: allegations of low-grade cheating, strange debates over sleeping temperature, and even some head-scratching behavior by athletes.\", \"from\": 1566, \"to\": 1808, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Games\", \"from\": 1590, \"to\": 1610}, {\"ngram\": \"plenty\", \"from\": 1654, \"to\": 1660}, {\"ngram\": \"bizarre drama\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1677}, {\"ngram\": \"allegations\", \"from\": 1679, \"to\": 1690}, {\"ngram\": \"low-grade cheating\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1712}, {\"ngram\": \"strange debates\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1729}, {\"ngram\": \"temperature\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1755}, {\"ngram\": \"even some head-scratching behavior\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1795}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1807}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's a quick guide to the controversies making headlines in the lead-up to the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1809, \"to\": 1902, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a quick guide\", \"from\": 1816, \"to\": 1829}, {\"ngram\": \"the controversies\", \"from\": 1833, \"to\": 1850}, {\"ngram\": \"headlines\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 1867}, {\"ngram\": \"the lead-up\", \"from\": 1871, \"to\": 1882}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 1886, \"to\": 1901}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the zaniest cheating scandals I have ever read about occurred on Monday, when officials from New Zealand's Olympic Committeereported that a flying dronewas circling the training facility of that country's women's soccer team during a practice session.\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 2162, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the zaniest cheating scandals\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1940}, {\"ngram\": \"Monday\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 1982}, {\"ngram\": \"officials\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 1998}, {\"ngram\": \"the training facility\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2097}, {\"ngram\": \"that country's women's soccer team\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2135}, {\"ngram\": \"a practice session\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2161}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They said this was actually the second drone flight to occur during training.\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2240, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the second drone flight\", \"from\": 2191, \"to\": 2214}, {\"ngram\": \"training\", \"from\": 2231, \"to\": 2239}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Local cops later tracked down the drone's pilot, who just so happened to be a staff member of Team Canada, the defending Olympic champions and a key rival of New Zealand.\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2412, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2336, \"end\": 2347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.999802720521863, \"rank\": 0.00019731840458083312, \"text\": \"Team Canada\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2400, \"end\": 2411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.8479209320018402, \"rank\": 0.179264122720552, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Local cops\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2251}, {\"ngram\": \"the drone's pilot\", \"from\": 2271, \"to\": 2288}, {\"ngram\": \"a staff member\", \"from\": 2317, \"to\": 2331}, {\"ngram\": \"the defending Olympic champions\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2379}, {\"ngram\": \"a key rival\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2395}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was swift recourse after the revelation-an investigation by the Canadian Olympic Committee determined that the squad had, indeed spied on New Zealand, and issued a public apology.\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2484, \"end\": 2510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canadian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2558, \"end\": 2569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.8479209320018402, \"rank\": 0.179264122720552, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"swift recourse\", \"from\": 2424, \"to\": 2438}, {\"ngram\": \"the revelation\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2459}, {\"ngram\": \"an investigation\", \"from\": 2460, \"to\": 2476}, {\"ngram\": \"the squad\", \"from\": 2527, \"to\": 2536}, {\"ngram\": \"a public apology\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2598}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Canada's head coach Bev Priestmanwas sent homejust before Canada played New Zealand (Canada won, 2:1), and two team staffers were also kicked out.\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2746, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2600, \"end\": 2606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999978326741, \"rank\": 2.1515403144609657e-09, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 2658, \"end\": 2664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999978326741, \"rank\": 2.1515403144609657e-09, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 2672, \"end\": 2683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.8479209320018402, \"rank\": 0.179264122720552, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2685, \"end\": 2691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999999978326741, \"rank\": 2.1515403144609657e-09, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bev Priestmanwas\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2636}, {\"ngram\": \"homejust\", \"from\": 2642, \"to\": 2650}, {\"ngram\": \"two team staffers\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2724}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition the Canadian Olympic Committee announced that the Canada Soccer staff would undergo ethics training after the incident.\", \"from\": 2747, \"to\": 2878, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2763, \"end\": 2789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Canadian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadian_Olympi